<p>I. Chain required after the contentChild, this eliminates undefined from the result type signature. If a required query does not find any results, Angular throws an error.</p>
<pre>private headerSubtitleContent = contentChild.required&lt;ElementRef&lt;HTMLAnchorElement&gt;&gt;('headerSubtitle');</pre>
<p>II. You can create a variable for the contentChild return value, after that the 'if' statement narrows the type of the value.</p>
<pre>effect(() =&gt; {
   let headerSubtitle = this.headerSubtitleContent();
   if (headerSubtitle) {
      headerSubtitle.nativeElement.textContent = 'HI this is my name';
     }
 });</pre>
